{%- comment -%}
  Renders product title prefixed with the selected/first available variant SKU:
    "{SKU} – {title}"
  When the variant has no SKU, returns only the title (no orphan dash).
  Separator: U+2013 (en dash) with surrounding spaces.

  Output is HTML-escaped via `| escape`, mirroring the original `{{ product.title | escape }}` usages this snippet replaces.

  NOTE: the snippet is purely presentational. It does not mutate product.title,
  meta tags, JSON-LD, URL handle or Shop App `data-shopify-title` — keep those
  bound to `product.title` directly.

  Param: `product` (Product object).

  Usage:
    {%- render 'product-display-title', product: product -%}
    {%- render 'product-display-title', product: card_product -%}
    {%- render 'product-display-title', product: item.product -%}
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- liquid
  assign _sku = product.selected_or_first_available_variant.sku
  if _sku != blank
    echo _sku | escape
    echo ' – '
  endif
  echo product.title | escape
-%}
